{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SurfaceEnergyFlux",
        "description": "Net surface heat flux and its derivative with respect to surface temperature for the urban canopy thermal column. Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:347 (`SurfaceEnergyFlux` @component). Implements Oleson et al. (2010, CLM Tech Note Ch. 4) Eqs. 4.26, 4.28, and 4.29: the surface heat flux h is the algebraic sum of absorbed solar radiation, net longwave radiation, sensible heat, latent heat, and waste/AC heat (Eq. 4.26); the longwave-derivative diagnostic dL_g_dT = 4*epsilon_g*sigma_SB*T_g_n^3 (Eq. 4.29) is the Stefan-Boltzmann temperature derivative of the upward longwave emission at the current surface temperature; the total flux derivative dh_dT = -dL_g_dT - dH_g_dT - dlambdaE_g_dT (Eq. 4.28) drives the linearized Crank-Nicholson scheme of Eq. 4.19. Parameterized as observed-only: S_g, L_g, H_g, lambdaE_g, H_wasteheat_g, H_aircond_g, epsilon_g, T_g_n, dH_g_dT, dlambdaE_g_dT are inputs (parameters); h, dL_g_dT, dh_dT are the algebraic state outputs.",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "temperatures",
            "surface_energy",
            "radiation",
            "observed-only",
            "clmu"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-12T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-xc7y)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., et al. (2010). Technical Description of version 4.0 of the Community Land Model (CLM). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-478+STR. Chapter 4, Section 4.4 (Urban surface energy balance), Eqs. 4.26-4.29, pp. 97-98."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SurfaceEnergyFlux": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:347\nUpstream `SurfaceEnergyFlux` is an MTK `@component` with ten `@parameters` (S_g, L_g, H_g, λE_g, H_wasteheat_g, H_aircond_g, ε_g, T_g_n, dH_g_dT, dλE_g_dT), two `@constants` (σ_SB = 5.67e-8 W/(m^2*K^4) and one_K = 1.0 K), three time-indexed `@variables` (h, dh_dT, dL_g_dT), and three algebraic equations (no derivatives). Identical equation structure preserved here. Upstream canonical test (test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:282) drives the three equations through `mtkcompile` + `ODEProblem` + `solve` and asserts the three outputs at fixed inputs; that fixture is reproduced verbatim here as the `upstream_equation_verification` test.\n\nThe upstream component declares two `@constants`, both encoded here as parameters with the upstream defaults: sigma_SB = 5.67e-8 W/(m^2*K^4) (Stefan-Boltzmann from Oleson Table 1.4) and one_K = 1.0 K (unit-balancer for the cube of T_g_n inside Eq. 4.29). Greek `σ_SB`, `ε_g`, `λE_g`, and `dλE_g_dT` are renamed `sigma_SB`, `epsilon_g`, `lambdaE_g`, and `dlambdaE_g_dT` for ASCII parameter names per the rig convention (matches the heating_cooling_flux.esm sibling's encoding of upstream `@constants` α_CN → alpha_CN; snow_density.esm uses rho_*).\n\nEq. 4.29 unit-balancing: the upstream form `4 * ε_g * σ_SB * (T_g_n / one_K)^3 * one_K^3` is preserved verbatim. The bare `T_g_n^3` would not work in MTK's symbolic algebra because the power operator demands a dimensionless exponent (here the literal `3`) act on a dimensionless base; `(T_g_n / one_K)^3` is dimensionless K/K cubed = dimensionless, and the trailing `* one_K^3` restores the K^3 needed to balance the W/(m^2*K^4) coefficient of `4*ε_g*σ_SB` against the W/(m^2*K) units of the LHS `dL_g_dT`. The runner observes the cube-of-cube structure as a chain of multiplies and one `^` op against the dimensionless quotient. The arithmetic value is identical to the unfused `4*ε_g*σ_SB*T_g_n^3` because one_K = 1.0 exactly, but the form is kept to mirror the upstream unit contract for any future ESS unit checker.\n\nEq. 4.26 sign convention: per the upstream description, h is the net heat flux INTO the surface (positive = energy gain). S_g is the absorbed solar radiation (positive = into the surface), L_g is the net longwave radiation in the convention where positive = net loss from the surface (consistent with the subtraction in the equation; the upstream description says `downward positive` but the equation form `h = S - L - ...` is loss-positive), H_g and lambdaE_g are upward sensible/latent fluxes (positive = loss from the surface), and the waste-heat and AC terms are additional energy inputs to the surface (positive = into the surface). The migrated ESM preserves the equation form exactly; the test `negative_net_longwave_heat_gain` pins the sign convention by exercising L_g < 0 (net longwave gain at the surface, h increases by |L_g|).\n\nObservability classification: this component is functionally observed-only — the three output variables are each given by a single algebraic equation in terms of the parameters (the `(t)` time index has no role since there are no derivatives). Test scenarios use `time_span: [0, 1]` and sample at t=0 to mirror the convention used by sibling observed-only ESM files in this rig (heating_cooling_flux.esm, phase_change_energy.esm, total_phase_change_energy.esm).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); Eqs. 4.26 and 4.28 are additive at IEEE-754 ULP precision (~1e-16) while Eq. 4.29 involves one `^3` op with similar ULP-level roundoff. 1e-9 leaves comfortable headroom and matches sibling temps files (heating_cooling_flux.esm uses 1e-9, phase_change_energy.esm uses 1e-9). Tighter `abs: 1e-12` is asserted on outputs that are exactly zero by construction (e.g. `epsilon_g = 0` → dL_g_dT = 0; all-zero flux inputs → h = 0) so the assertion does not silently accept a stuck-at-1e-3 regression.\n\nUpstream tolerance reproduction: upstream canonical test uses `rtol = 1.0e-10` on h (purely additive) and `rtol = 1.0e-6` on dL_g_dT and dh_dT (both involve the cube). Re-asserted at the same tolerances via per-assertion `tolerance` blocks on the upstream-canonical test, tighter than the model-level default for h."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-9
            },
            "variables": {
                "sigma_SB": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/(m^2*K^4)",
                    "default": 5.67e-8,
                    "description": "Stefan-Boltzmann constant (Oleson Table 1.4) — upstream `@constants` σ_SB; the coefficient of the T^3 derivative of the Stefan-Boltzmann law for upward longwave emission used in Eq. 4.29"
                },
                "one_K": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Unit-temperature reference (1 K) — upstream `@constants` one_K; used in `(T_g_n / one_K)^3 * one_K^3` to make the cube of T_g_n unit-consistent with MTK's symbolic unit algebra (dimensionless base for the exponent, then restored K^3 for the outer dimension). Value is exactly 1.0 by construction; numerically a no-op."
                },
                "S_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Absorbed solar radiation at the surface (Oleson Eq. 4.26 first term) — net shortwave absorbed by the surface, positive into the surface"
                },
                "L_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Net longwave radiation at the surface (Oleson Eq. 4.26 second term) — net upward longwave emission convention (positive = loss from the surface); subtracted in h"
                },
                "H_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Sensible heat flux at the surface (Oleson Eq. 4.26 third term) — turbulent sensible heat loss from the surface to the atmosphere, positive = loss; subtracted in h"
                },
                "lambdaE_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Latent heat flux at the surface (Oleson Eq. 4.26 fourth term) — upstream `@parameters` λE_g; turbulent latent heat loss from the surface to the atmosphere, positive = loss; subtracted in h"
                },
                "H_wasteheat_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Waste heat flux applied to this surface (Oleson Eq. 4.26 fifth term) — anthropogenic waste-heat input from buildings, positive into the surface"
                },
                "H_aircond_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Air-conditioning heat flux applied to this surface (Oleson Eq. 4.26 sixth term) — anthropogenic AC-driven heat rejection input, positive into the surface"
                },
                "epsilon_g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.95,
                    "description": "Surface emissivity (dimensionless) — upstream `@parameters` ε_g; coefficient on the Stefan-Boltzmann upward emission in Eq. 4.29. Typical urban surfaces 0.85-0.98; default 0.95 matches upstream test fixture"
                },
                "T_g_n": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 300.0,
                    "description": "Surface temperature at time n (Oleson Eq. 4.29) — input from the column-temperature solution at the start of the implicit-explicit step; cubed in the dL_g_dT derivative diagnostic"
                },
                "dH_g_dT": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/(m^2*K)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Partial derivative of sensible heat flux with respect to T_g (Oleson Eq. 4.28) — supplied by an upstream turbulence/aerodynamic-resistance subsystem; enters dh_dT with a negative sign"
                },
                "dlambdaE_g_dT": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/(m^2*K)",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Partial derivative of latent heat flux with respect to T_g (Oleson Eq. 4.28) — upstream `@parameters` dλE_g_dT; supplied by the surface-flux subsystem (depends on saturation-vapor-pressure derivative); enters dh_dT with a negative sign"
                },
                "h": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "description": "Net heat flux into the surface (Oleson Eq. 4.26): h = S_g - L_g - H_g - lambdaE_g + H_wasteheat_g + H_aircond_g; positive = net energy gain by the surface"
                },
                "dL_g_dT": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "W/(m^2*K)",
                    "description": "Partial derivative of net longwave emission with respect to T_g (Oleson Eq. 4.29): 4*epsilon_g*sigma_SB*T_g_n^3; always non-negative because epsilon_g, sigma_SB, and T_g_n^3 are non-negative; characterizes the radiative-feedback strength of the surface temperature solver"
                },
                "dh_dT": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "W/(m^2*K)",
                    "description": "Partial derivative of total surface heat flux with respect to T_g (Oleson Eq. 4.28): -dL_g_dT - dH_g_dT - dlambdaE_g_dT; drives the linearized Crank-Nicholson surface-temperature update (Eq. 4.19) — typically negative because warming the surface increases outgoing radiative and turbulent losses"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "h",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "-",
                                                "args": [
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "-",
                                                        "args": ["S_g", "L_g"]
                                                    },
                                                    "H_g"
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "lambdaE_g"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "H_wasteheat_g"
                                ]
                            },
                            "H_aircond_g"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "dL_g_dT",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [4.0, "epsilon_g"]
                                            },
                                            "sigma_SB"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "^",
                                        "args": [
                                            { "op": "/", "args": ["T_g_n", "one_K"] },
                                            3.0
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "^",
                                "args": ["one_K", 3.0]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "dh_dT",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [
                                    { "op": "-", "args": [0.0, "dL_g_dT"] },
                                    "dH_g_dT"
                                ]
                            },
                            "dlambdaE_g_dT"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "upstream_equation_verification",
                    "description": "Reproduces upstream `SurfaceEnergyFlux - Equation Verification` test (UrbanCanopy.jl test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:282). Canonical inputs: S_g = 200, L_g = 50, H_g = 30, lambdaE_g = 20, H_wasteheat_g = 10, H_aircond_g = 5, epsilon_g = 0.95, T_g_n = 300, dH_g_dT = 5, dlambdaE_g_dT = 2. Expected: h = 200 - 50 - 30 - 20 + 10 + 5 = 115 W/m^2 (Eq. 4.26); dL_g_dT = 4*0.95*5.67e-8*300^3 = 5.81742 W/(m^2*K) (Eq. 4.29); dh_dT = -5.81742 - 5 - 2 = -12.81742 W/(m^2*K) (Eq. 4.28). Tolerances mirror upstream: rtol = 1.0e-10 on h (purely additive) and rtol = 1.0e-6 on the two cube-based outputs.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": 50.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 5.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.95,
                        "T_g_n": 300.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 5.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "h",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 115.0,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-10 }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dL_g_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 5.81742,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dh_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -12.81742,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "all_zero_inputs",
                    "description": "Degenerate boundary: every flux parameter and derivative is zero, T_g_n = 0 K, epsilon_g = 0. h = 0 (additive identity), dL_g_dT = 4 * 0 * sigma_SB * 0^3 = 0 exactly, dh_dT = -0 - 0 - 0 = 0. Anchors the all-zero result of the merged equations and exercises the runner against epsilon_g = 0 and T_g_n = 0 simultaneously (each independently zeros dL_g_dT — verifies neither raises an underflow / divide-by-zero error).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 0.0,
                        "L_g": 0.0,
                        "H_g": 0.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 0.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 0.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 0.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.0,
                        "T_g_n": 0.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 0.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "dL_g_dT", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "dh_dT",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "zero_emissivity_no_radiative_feedback",
                    "description": "Boundary case: epsilon_g = 0 (perfectly reflective, hypothetical limit). The longwave-derivative term vanishes: dL_g_dT = 4 * 0 * sigma_SB * T_g_n^3 * 1 = 0 exactly regardless of T_g_n. The radiative feedback in dh_dT therefore collapses to dh_dT = -dH_g_dT - dlambdaE_g_dT = -5 - 2 = -7 W/(m^2*K). h is unaffected by epsilon_g (it does not appear in Eq. 4.26). Isolates the epsilon_g pre-factor of Eq. 4.29.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": 50.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 5.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.0,
                        "T_g_n": 300.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 5.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 115.0 },
                        { "variable": "dL_g_dT", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "dh_dT",   "time": 0.0, "expected": -7.0 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "blackbody_epsilon_one",
                    "description": "Boundary case: epsilon_g = 1 (blackbody upper limit). dL_g_dT = 4 * 1 * 5.67e-8 * 300^3 = 6.1236 W/(m^2*K) — the largest possible radiative feedback at T_g_n = 300 K. dh_dT = -6.1236 - 5 - 2 = -13.1236 W/(m^2*K). Anchors the upper bound of the radiative-feedback magnitude and verifies that the equation is linear in epsilon_g (the ratio dL_g_dT(epsilon=1) / dL_g_dT(epsilon=0.95) = 1/0.95 ≈ 1.0526; both are reported, so a reviewer can cross-check).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": 50.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 5.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 1.0,
                        "T_g_n": 300.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 5.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 115.0 },
                        {
                            "variable": "dL_g_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 6.1236,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dh_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -13.1236,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "zero_surface_temperature_no_radiation",
                    "description": "Boundary case: T_g_n = 0 K (unphysical but mathematically valid in the equation). dL_g_dT = 4 * 0.95 * 5.67e-8 * 0^3 * 1 = 0 exactly — the cube zeroes out the entire radiative-derivative term regardless of epsilon_g. dh_dT = -0 - dH_g_dT - dlambdaE_g_dT = -5 - 2 = -7 W/(m^2*K). Exercises the cube power against zero and confirms IEEE-754 0^3 = 0 (no NaN/Inf branch).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": 50.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 5.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.95,
                        "T_g_n": 0.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 5.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 115.0 },
                        { "variable": "dL_g_dT", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } },
                        { "variable": "dh_dT",   "time": 0.0, "expected": -7.0 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cold_surface_lower_radiative_feedback",
                    "description": "Realistic cold-surface case: T_g_n = 250 K (e.g. nighttime urban canyon in winter). dL_g_dT = 4 * 0.95 * 5.67e-8 * 250^3 = 3.3665625 W/(m^2*K) — substantially smaller than at 300 K because of the cube scaling (T^3 ratio = (250/300)^3 ≈ 0.579). dh_dT = -3.3665625 - 5 - 2 = -10.3665625 W/(m^2*K). Surfaces the cube-of-temperature scaling that dominates the seasonal variation of the radiative feedback term.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": 50.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 5.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.95,
                        "T_g_n": 250.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 5.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 115.0 },
                        {
                            "variable": "dL_g_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 3.3665625,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dh_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -10.3665625,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "hot_surface_higher_radiative_feedback",
                    "description": "Realistic hot-surface case: T_g_n = 350 K (e.g. midsummer sunlit asphalt). dL_g_dT = 4 * 0.95 * 5.67e-8 * 350^3 = 9.2378475 W/(m^2*K) — substantially larger than at 300 K. dh_dT = -9.2378475 - 5 - 2 = -16.2378475 W/(m^2*K). Pairs with `cold_surface_lower_radiative_feedback` to surface the monotone increase of |dh_dT| with T_g_n (warmer surfaces have stronger negative feedback, stabilizing the implicit Crank-Nicholson update).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": 50.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 5.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.95,
                        "T_g_n": 350.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 5.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 115.0 },
                        {
                            "variable": "dL_g_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 9.2378475,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dh_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -16.2378475,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "wasteheat_and_aircond_isolated",
                    "description": "Isolates the anthropogenic-heat terms: all natural fluxes zero (S_g = L_g = H_g = lambdaE_g = 0) with H_wasteheat_g = 50 W/m^2 and H_aircond_g = 25 W/m^2. h = 0 - 0 - 0 - 0 + 50 + 25 = 75 W/m^2. epsilon_g and T_g_n still drive dL_g_dT and dh_dT as before. Anchors the additive contribution of the urban anthropogenic terms in Eq. 4.26 — these distinguish the CLMU urban-canopy energy balance from the underlying CLM natural-surface energy balance.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 0.0,
                        "L_g": 0.0,
                        "H_g": 0.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 0.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 50.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 25.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.95,
                        "T_g_n": 300.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 0.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 75.0 },
                        {
                            "variable": "dL_g_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 5.81742,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "dh_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": -5.81742,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "negative_net_longwave_heat_gain",
                    "description": "Regime check: L_g = -30 W/m^2 (more incoming longwave than outgoing — e.g. cloudy night surface emitting less than the atmosphere emits downward). The subtraction `-L_g = -(-30) = +30` adds to h, giving h = 200 - (-30) - 30 - 20 + 10 + 5 = 195 W/m^2. Confirms the sign convention of Eq. 4.26: negative L_g represents net longwave gain at the surface and is correctly handled by the signed subtraction.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": -30.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
                        "H_aircond_g": 5.0,
                        "epsilon_g": 0.95,
                        "T_g_n": 300.0,
                        "dH_g_dT": 5.0,
                        "dlambdaE_g_dT": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "h",       "time": 0.0, "expected": 195.0 },
                        {
                            "variable": "dL_g_dT",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 5.81742,
                            "tolerance": { "rel": 1.0e-6 }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "zero_turbulent_derivatives_only_radiative_feedback",
                    "description": "dH_g_dT = dlambdaE_g_dT = 0 isolates the radiative term in Eq. 4.28: dh_dT = -dL_g_dT - 0 - 0 = -5.81742 W/(m^2*K) at canonical T_g_n = 300, epsilon_g = 0.95. Exercises the no-turbulence limit of the surface-temperature solver feedback and confirms additive structure of Eq. 4.28.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_g": 200.0,
                        "L_g": 50.0,
                        "H_g": 30.0,
                        "lambdaE_g": 20.0,
                        "H_wasteheat_g": 10.0,
